<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1290,1531]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1290,1315]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head with a distinct, tumid postocular portion, eyes separated from anterior margin of pronotum but not stalked; distiflagellum at most slightly longer than (0.8–1.3 times as long as) pedicel; scutellum with a distinct Tshaped carina, adjacent lateral foveae with large, coarse, confluent punctures; metathoracic scent gland provided with well developed, protruding peritreme; fore femur unarmed (
<bibRefCitation author="Pericart" box="[877,1033,1398,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" refString="Pericart, J. (1999) Hemipteres Lygaeidae Euro-Mediterraneens. Vol 1. Faune de France. 84 A. Federation Francaise des Societes de Sciences Naturelles, Paris, 468 pp." type="book" year="1999">Péricart 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gao" box="[1043,1221,1398,1423]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" refString="Gao, C. Q., Kondorosy, E. &amp; Bu, W. J. (2013) A review of the genus Arocatus from Palaearctic and Oriental Regions (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Lygaeidae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 61 (2), 687 - 704." type="journal article" year="2013">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[1097,1153,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="239" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1290,1531]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,517,1434,1459]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Distribution and diversity.</emphasis>
The genus is distributed in the Palaearctic, Afrotropical, 
<collectingRegion box="[1170,1262,1434,1459]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">Oriental</collectingRegion>
and Australian Regions and currently contains 18 described species (
<bibRefCitation author="Gao" box="[774,963,1470,1495]" pageId="1" pageNumber="239" refString="Gao, C. Q., Kondorosy, E. &amp; Bu, W. J. (2013) A review of the genus Arocatus from Palaearctic and Oriental Regions (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Lygaeidae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 61 (2), 687 - 704." type="journal article" year="2013">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[832,891,1470,1495]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="239">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). An additional new species is described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
